title: The Assasination
author: c0c0nut
pages:
#- 

      Assasination
            of
      King Wilhelm I
       of Prussia
#- I entered the throne room with cold blood.

#- I had known from my previous investigations that the wool right behind the throne was only iron reinforced. My plan was to abuse this mistake.
#- I grabbed my efficiency pick and started hacking the wool away.
#- If I wanted to enter the throne area, I had to break two pieces of wool. 

Maybe I could reach the king with my sword without entering the area? That would save the hassle of breaking an iron reinforced wool block.
#- As soon as I broke the wool block on top, I started hitting the one in the bottom. I had only hit it a few times when the King noticed me. He started walking towards me. He had a "WTF ARE YOU DOING PLEB" espression in his ugly little face.
#- With swift movements, he jumped out of the throne area using the 1 block gap I had made earlier. The King was only a few centimeters away from me at that moment. From his panicked steps and wing moves I figured he was going to attempt to call the guards.
#- I could not let that happen.

It was time.

I grabbed my sword. It took me only one hit to deal with the King. 

And just like that, I killed the King, on 
12th of April, 2013.
#- I was holding the corpse of His Majesty with an evil smirk on my face.

Oh how puny, how miserable he looked now...
#- I quickly put a decoy chicken in the place of the King using a spawn egg, then replaced the wool block I had removed. After that I proceeded to steal all the heir eggs and put plebian chicken eggs in their places.

#- Right now, the crime scene looks perfectly ordinary.

But they have snitches which they check regularly. They will know soon.

I don't have much time left.
#- 